When I got my GBS, I was ready to log, but stood up for one last look-see.  And there was Pyzjn right in the middle of the ruins with pet!  I must have been asleep or something, because I was surprised to see she had time to make her pet without me hearing the cast.  She did not walk up to the ruins, or I would have seen her.<br>
<br>
I've killed her five times, twice in the ruins, three times walking to the ruins.  Only once did she drop the GBS while in the ruins.  I've also heard of others getting the stone without her being in the ruins.<br>
<br>
So, maybe there's a 10% probability of her dropping the stone <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  AWAY</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> from the ruins, and a 50%(?) probability of dropping it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  AT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the ruins.  After reading most of the accounts of aquiring the GBS, most people just casually run up to the ruins, kill Pyzjn in the ruins, and she drops the stone.  There is reason to believe that she has a higher drop rate while in the ruins.  She doesn't drop it all the time in the ruins, but it may be significantly higher than while she's walking to them.<br>
<br>
