<br>
Your first point is a most common one.  After every patch, there are always those that will start a rumor that the GBS doesn't drop anymore.  It's due to frustration and lack of getting the coveted stone after many hundreds of boring hours camping Pyzjn.  Believe me, the GBS still drops.  I got one right after someone said that it didn't drop anymore due to a patch.  Lol.<br>
<br>
Your second point is an urban legend.  These types of things are common when someone likes to instill doubt and chaos into an environment that already holds a certain degree of longing to believe that the falsehood is true.  It stems from lack of knowledge or just plain stupidity.  I have yet to see ANY type of quest work to obtain the GBS.  And from the data that I've collected on Pyzjn, her drop rate, and her spawn rate, I've come to the conclusion that she is similar to the Ancient Cyclops that drops the ring for the Jboot quest.  Basically, the drop of the GBS is like the drop of the ring: they are not on a timed drop table.  Both drops are rare enough that they could be considered &quot;random.&quot;<br>
<br>
Those that claim that there is a quest have NEVER stepped forward to show its truth.  Excuses will be made that making public the quest would drive GBS prices down.  This is simply a cover of the cowardice that these people have.<br>
<br>
I'm just sick and tired of misinformation distributed about this drop.  If you're going to try and get it, JUST DO IT! <p><i><b><font face="ARIAL" size="2" color="#FF0000">
~~~Xaxia Pi~~~<BR>On her 26th Pie<BR>Lanys T’Vyl<BR><BR>Master Butcher - "That staff's got one hell of a proc! - Thimblerig, commenting on my Water Crystal Staff"<BR><BR>Master Baker - "Whoever gives me brownie parts will be put into my will."<BR><BR>Master Candlestickmaker - "I'd like 50 stones of hot wax there, yes, right there!"</font></b>
